{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Variables (Entity SQL)\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: 3eed222a-f8f6-46b6-9cd5-220cc0e4e5d8\n---\n# Variables (Entity SQL)\n## Variable  \n A variable expression is a reference to a named expression defined in the current scope. A variable reference must be a valid [!INCLUDE[esql](../../../../../../includes/esql-md.md)] identifier, as defined in [Identifiers](../../../../../../docs/framework/data/adonet/ef/language-reference/identifiers-entity-sql.md).  \n  \n The following example shows the use of a variable in the expression. The `c` in the FROM clause is the definition of the variable. The use of `c` in the SELECT clause represents the variable reference.  \n  \n```  \nselect c   \nfrom LOB.customers as c  \n```  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [Identifiers](../../../../../../docs/framework/data/adonet/ef/language-reference/identifiers-entity-sql.md)\n- [Parameters](../../../../../../docs/framework/data/adonet/ef/language-reference/parameters-entity-sql.md)\n- [Entity SQL Overview](../../../../../../docs/framework/data/adonet/ef/language-reference/entity-sql-overview.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,106],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Variables (Entity SQL)\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.assetid: 3eed222a-f8f6-46b6-9cd5-220cc0e4e5d8","nodes":[{"content":"Variables (Entity SQL)","nodes":[{"pos":[0,22],"content":"Variables (Entity SQL)","nodes":[{"content":"Variables (Entity SQL)","pos":[0,22]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[113,135],"content":"Variables (Entity SQL)","linkify":"Variables (Entity SQL)","nodes":[{"content":"Variables (Entity SQL)","pos":[0,22]}]},{"pos":[139,147],"content":"Variable","linkify":"Variable","nodes":[{"content":"Variable","pos":[0,8]}]},{"content":"A variable expression is a reference to a named expression defined in the current scope.","pos":[151,239]},{"content":"A variable reference must be a valid <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[esql](../../../../../../includes/esql-md.md)